                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5031: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_DJW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-14T20:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 14, 1919, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:38 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2798. Following from [<persName corresp="#p_CF1">Cole</persName> at]
                    Archangel:</p>
                <p>“1377, August 13, 6 p.m. The entire Bolshevik force on the Dvina River consisting
                    of 6,000 was either captured, killed or scattered by an attack on Sunday carried
                    out by about 3,000 British and 1,000 Russians who moved forward in the forests
                    on both sides of the river completely outflanking all Bolshevik positions. Up to
                    last night 1,840 prisoners have been registered and several hundred more are to
                    come in. Bolshevik casualties were very heavy; 12 field guns, a large number of
                    machine guns, 2,000 rifles and much ammunition was captured. The British
                    intelligence bureau states that there are now no effective Bolshevik forces
                    between our front and Kotka [<hi rend="italic">Kotlas?</hi>]. <persName
                        corresp="#p_CF1">Cole</persName>.[”]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
